21:18.296 --> 21:27.369
But then a young American named Dick Fosbury at the age of 21 on October 20th, 1968 won the gold medal and set an Olympic record.

21:27.449 --> 21:28.210
How did he do that?

21:28.891 --> 21:37.202
By using a technique that no one had seen before, she rather than going face down her feet first, Fosbury turned his back to the bar, arched his back,

21:37.474 --> 21:40.639
and kicked his legs up and out.

21:40.679 --> 21:47.971
Now broadcasters and coaches were stunned, fans didn't know what to think, and so they called it the Fosbury Flop.

21:48.032 --> 21:52.759
No one had done this before, and now almost 60 years later, it's the only technique that high jumpers use.

21:53.200 --> 21:57.708
